FBIS3-47864 "dreas014_i_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 Cambodia Khmer Rouge: U.S. Finances Psychological Warfare BK1901025594 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 18 Jan 94 BK1901025594 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union Front of Cambodia Language: Cambodian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] There are reports saying that the two-heads-three-eyes government plans to send airplanes to distribute many signed leaflets over the battlefields around Tonle Sap lake and the northwest and northern parts of Cambodia under the control of Democratic Kampuchea. The aim is to urge patriotic fighters to lay down their weapons and surrender. This is psychological warfare against the Cambodian nation and people, national reconciliation, and the king's five-point proposal. The alliance -- the United States, Australia, and France -- especially the United States and Australia are the financiers of this dirty psychological warfare. [passage omitted] This kind of psychological warfare has been shamefully and successively exposed, and it will certainly face more serious failures because the people oppose it. [passage omitted]
